header.gameNote: WORLD VISION CLASSIC AT LAS VEGAS

article.description: Kelsey Bone scored a career-high 33 points to lead No. 22 Texas A&M to a 78-55 win over Old Dominion in the World Vision Classic on Thursday night.
article.headline: Kelsey Bone scores career-high 33 to lift Texas A&ampM
article.linkText: Bone scores career-high 33 to lift Texas A&ampM
article.story:
LAS VEGAS --  Kelsey Bone scored a career-high 33 points to lead No. 22 Texas A&M to a 78-55 win over Old Dominion in the World Vision Classic on Thursday night.

Bone was 15 of 18 from the field and had 14 rebounds in her double-double performance.

Kristi Bellock scored 12 points, and Peyton Little came off the bench to score 10 points. Adrienne Pratcher had 12 assists.

The Aggies led 36-28 at halftime. The Aggies (8-3) shot 32 of 72 (44.4 percent) from the field, while Old Dominion (7-2) shot 23 of 54 (42.6 percent).

Shae Kelley led the Lady Monarchs with 11 points and seven rebounds. Jackie Cook had 10 points.
